<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Justin Bieber and his wife Hailey celebrated their wedding anniversary on Wednesday by taking to Instagram.</p>

<p>Both the Sorry singer and the Vogue model posted stunning black-and-white photos from their splashy nuptials.</p>

<p>While the crooner said he was 'lucky' to be the beauty's husband, the cover girl shared she wishes she could relive their wedding day.</p>

<p>Wedded bliss: Justin Bieber and his wife Hailey celebrated their wedding anniversary on Wednesday by taking to Instagram</p>

<p>Elegant affair: Both the Sorry singer and the Vogue model posted stunning black-and-white photos from their splashy nuptials</p>

<p>The power couple married for the first time at a courthouse in New York City on September 13, 2018. </p>

<p>Then on September 20, 2019 they had a big wedding at the Montage Palmetto Bluff, a 20,000-acre luxury waterfront resort in South Carolina. </p>

<p>Justin started, 'Hailey Bieber. I am so lucky to be YOUR husband!'</p>

<p>The Company hitmaker also said: 'You teach me so much everyday and make me such a better man! </p>

<p>It's true love! While the crooner said he was 'lucky' to be the beauty's husband, the cover girl shared she wishes she could relive their wedding day</p>

<p>Two wedding dates: The power couple married for the first time at a courthouse in New York City on September 13, 2018. Then on September 20, 2019 they had a big wedding at the Montage Palmetto Bluff, a 20,000-acre luxury waterfront resort in South Carolina</p>

<p>'I am committed for the rest of our lives to empower you to be the woman God has called you to be! </p>

<p>'My heart is to enable you to achieve all of your wildest dreams!'</p>

<p>Then he said he would never take the catwalk queen for granted: 'I promise to always put you first, to lead with patience and kindness!! Happy anniversary my beautiful sweet girl.'</p>

<p>The blonde then had her say: '1 year ago we had the best wedding. Wish I could live this day over and over.'</p>

<p>Gushy note: Justin started, 'Hailey Bieber. I am so lucky to be YOUR husband!' The Company hitmaker also said: 'You teach me so much everyday and make me such a better man!'</p>

<p>This comes after Bieber and Chance the Rapper announced they are giving away $250,000 to fans in need.</p>

<p>The two stars have decided to mark their collaboration 'Holy' reaching number one on the iTunes chart by helping out those affected by 'these hard times' on Cash App, and urged those who are seeking financial assistance to tell their stories on social media.</p>

<p>Justin and Chance shared identical posts on their Twitter and Instagram accounts which read: 'Thanks for the love on 'Holy'.</p>

<p>'[We're] partnering with Cash App to give away a total of $250k today to those affected by these hard times.</p>

<p>So happy: Then he said he would never take the catwalk queen for granted: 'I promise to always put you first, to lead with patience and kindness!! Happy anniversary my beautiful sweet girl'</p>

<p>'Tell us your story if you feel like sharing. To enter drop your $cashtag &amp; use #JBChanceHoly.'</p>

<p>One fan, Katy, sent a message to Justin to tell him about the damage her home suffered due to Hurricane Laura last month, and was rewarded with $500 shortly afterwards.</p>

<p>She tweeted: 'my house, my mothers house, and my boyfriends house all suffered so many damages indoor and outdoor from #HurricaneLaura on august 27. anything is greatly appreciated.(sic)'</p>

<p>She then shared a screenshot of the donation and wrote in another tweet: 'JUSTIN I AM SOBBING AND SHAKING AT WORK YOU HAVE NO IDEA HOW MUCH THIS WILL HELP US! Thank you SO MUCH! I COULD NEVER THANK YOU ENOUGH! LOVE YOU SO MUCH! #JBCHANCEHOLY.(sic)'</p>

<p>Twice as nice: This comes after Bieber and Chance the Rapper announced they are giving away $250,000 to fans in need</p>

<p>Dozens of others shared messages on the platform expressing their delight for the two stars for helping them out with college tuition, debts, support for their families and other reasons.</p>

<p>Justin and Chance dropped 'Holy' - the first song from the 26-year-old star since his studio album 'Changes', which was released in February - a week ago, with the 'Believe' hitmaker proclaiming at the time he was heralding in a 'new era' with the gospel-tinged collaboration.</p>

<p>Taking to Instagram, Justin wrote alongside the artwork: 'New era. New single. It's begins. #HOLY this Friday ft. <?php echo e('@'); ?>chancetherapper jbsoon.com.'</p>
